5:
The final adjustments have been
made to the body. Regis, do you
have it?
8:
Of course. As promised, I've installed
the final learning processes and
included all the memories from their
time spent separated.
12:
To think such a small thing is what
defines your soul. I'm always
fascinated, no matter how many
times I see it.
16:
Haha, is it so fascinating? You get to
see it at work whenever you meet
me.
20: It's time to wake up, my dear.
22:
Will you become a god of
destruction like before? Or will
something else take root in your
heart?
26:
Hahaha, all we ask is that you do as
you please. Welcome to the world of
people!
34:
What the hell did you do?! Spit it
out—now!
39:
Urk... You could show at least a little
concern... It's been a while since I
was so thoroughly thrashed!
44:
Listen, we didn't intend for things to
get so out of hand—
47:
Heheh, you're both finally here!
Mama Nate! Mama Themis!
51: ...I'm sorry, did you just say MAMA?!
55:
As disappointed as I am to admit it, I
don't remember having a child with
Nate. So that begs the question...
Who are you?
60:
You don't remember? Aren't you just
the worst mamas in the world! Or
maybe your brains are faulty?
63:
Just kidding. This is your first time
seeing this form, so of course you
don't remember. I'll give my
wonderful mamas a hint—you
destroyed me once before!
69:
Aww, how pathetic! Tell me—what's
it like to be weaker than a synthetic
pet?
72:
You've got nothing to worry about
though. I'm the type of god who's
super kind and compassionate!
76:
As long as you don't get in the way
of my world domination, that is.
86:
Ahahaha! Is this the best you can
do, Mamas? I almost feel sorry for
you!
90:
Beg for your lives, and maybe I'll
spare them! Or you can just DIE!
99:
Huh?! How'd you cut off my
connection?!
104:
Got you! Now hold still, and don't try
anything funny!
110:
Who died and made you boss? Let...
go... of me!
115:
Behave. Cause any more
destruction and we won't go easy
on you, even if you're a child.
125:
WAAAHHH! Why does humanity
always have to get in my way?!
131:
What the hell? You're gonna cry over
that of all things?
134:
You can set her down, Nate. The
safety systems are preventing her
from more hacking.
137:
Sheesh, you're too cute to be
messing around like this. Here, wipe
your tears and blow your nose.
140:
Sorry for being so rough with you.
Are you hurt? Not that I think you
are, but I figured I'd ask.
145:
*sniffle* Hmph! As if weaklings like
you could do damage to me!
148:
Yeah, yeah, guess that means you're
fine. I've got other questions for you,
then.
150:
What'd he say your name was?
Stinelle? Who are you, and why'd
you call us your "mamas"?
161:
You put the Unification AI—the same
one that almost destroyed us—into
a synthetic body?!
164:
I thought the AI got wiped when we
destroyed that machine...
168:
We never said there wasn't a
backup copy!
173:
Would it kill you to stop the stupid
antics for one second, you moron?!
177:
B-but you're the one who wanted
the AI to experience life as a person.
184:
I hope you get another chance to
live among us and see who we
really are.
188:
...Crap, I said that, didn't I... This is my
fault...
192:
So that's why she calls you her
mama. But I don't understand. Why
me as well?
195:
My personality was largely
influenced by data collected from
your emotional receptors.
199:
Hehehe, I also have other data
too—like a video of Mama Nate
crying and saying a ton of
embarrassing things in her room!
204:
You what?! That's... That's an
invasion of privacy!
214: HEY! Don't try to buy it off her!
219:
...Are you really sure about this?
We're talking about an AI that has a
track record for violence here.
224:
Hahaha, you see, she has what we
androids all hold sacred—a
manabrain that serves as her soul.
229:
Though I mentioned a backup
earlier, the truth is that this child
contains the main unit.
232:
The AI that ran rampant was
connected to her memory,
accumulating the data necessary to
induce growth.
236:
Are you telling me... that whole plot
was an experiment to raise Stinelle?
241:
By the way, her synthetic body is top
of the line haute couture from a
name brand! Isn't she just the cutest
little button?
245:
So there you have it. She might have
the data from the AI that went wild,
but she still has the right to her own
future.
248:
Plus, well, we really don't have the
time to look after her, what with the
cleanup from the mess earlier.
Could you do it instead?
254:
*sigh* Why did I have a feeling this
was coming...
260:
Stop pushing! I can walk on my own!
Where are you taking me anyway—
269:
You're an android, right? Don't you
recognize another world when you
see one?
274:
How would I? Do YOU have
memories from when you were a
baby?!
279:
When I first utilized you, even I didn't
know you were from another world.
There's so much out there to
discover.
281:
Explore it all to your heart's content.
If you find that you reach the same
conclusion as before, then we'll face
you once more.
286:
...Hmph, I won't change my mind.
You'll see.
290:
Look at her, all curious but refusing
to admit it.
296:
From this day forward, I, Stinelle
Obstinator, will live here against my
own will!
299:
You'll take care of me, won't you? I'll
be your future god, after all.
